Shares of the following companies
had unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses, and prices are as of the noon close in
Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index climbed 0.2 percent to
3,737.04, the first gain in six days.  Copper producers:  Philex Mining Corp . (PX PM), the nationâ€™s
biggest producer of the metal, gained 3 percent to 15.24 pesos,
the steepest gain since Jan. 25, as copper rose for a second day
in London.  Atlas Consolidated Mining & Development  Corp. (AT PM)
rose 0.8 percent to 15.18 pesos, the most since Feb. 14.    Ayala Land Inc . (ALI PM), the largest builder, fell 0.4
percent to 14.38 pesos, the lowest since Feb. 11. The company
said it will borrow as much as 2 billion pesos ($46 million)
through the sale of three-year notes in a public offering.  To contact the reporter on this story:
